    {
      "id": "3159408866bbae92fd66062c9f98b967899d8b2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-07 22:05:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThese patches should probably have been pushed separately instead of in a series, since they are all independent.\n\nYou could quickly \"Rebase\" in Gerrit and select \"Change parent revision\" and leave it empty to rebase to master.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "717ff3d4094e2573b701b19c97dd83b7e6463207",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-07 22:09:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> These patches should probably have been pushed separately instead of in a series, since they are all independent.\n> \n> You could quickly \"Rebase\" in Gerrit and select \"Change parent revision\" and leave it empty to rebase to master.\n\nI guess if they do diverge I could do that, so far just updating the patches that needed updating produced good enough results I think?\n\n(git rebase, change pick to edit in the middle of the series, it stops there, you amend the patch and push it before rebase completion, then run rebase --continue to get back to the top. This way if any more patches need any more changes that are further down the line - they automatically would be rebased to the latest version of the prior patches too.)\n\nI guess the only downside is if the testing fails in the middle of the series the rest of them would not be shown as ready for landing, but we probably don't care much about testing here anyway?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b27ad64866050b580250db4998a33ebe310c3472",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-07 22:14:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I guess the only downside is if the testing fails in the middle of\n > the series the rest of them would not be shown as ready for\n > landing, but we probably don't care much about testing here anyway?\n\nOr some intermediate patch could be held up by reviews, etc.  If they don't pass testing, they will never show up in the list of \"ready\" patches...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
